!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = library type: mRNA
!Sample_molecule_ch1 = polyA RNA
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = The single-cell RNA-Seq of FACS-sorted cell suspensions was performed on Chromium instrument (10X genomics) following the user guide manual for 3â² v3.1. In brief, FACS-sorted cells were washed once with PBS containing 1% bovine serum albumin (BSA) and resuspended in PBS containing 1% BSA to a final concentration of 700â1,300 cells per Î¼l. The viability of cells was above 80%, as confirmed with 0.2% (w/v) Trypan Blue staining (Countess II). Cells were captured in droplets.
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = Following reverse transcription and cell barcoding in droplets, emulsions were broken and cDNA purified using Dynabeads MyOne SILANE followed by PCR amplification per manual instruction. Around 10,000 cells were targeted for each sample. Samples were sometimes multiplexed together on one lane of 10X Chromium (using Hash Tag Oligonucleotides - HTO)  and specific extracellular protein epitope characterized (using Antibody Derived Tag - ADT)
!Sample_description = Library name: SH-2852_11_1 rna
!Sample_data_processing = CellRanger count pipeline
!Sample_data_processing = Assembly: GRCh38
!Sample_data_processing = Supplementary files format and content: CellRanger output files
